longBusinessSummary: Niraku GC Holdings, Inc., an investment holding company, engages in the operation of pachinko and pachislot halls in Japan. The company also operates a Spanish restaurant franchise under the LIZARRAN brand name; cafes under the KOMEDA brand name; a food court under the YOKOCHO brand name; and tea café under the Gong Cha brand name, as well as hotels and amusement arcade. In addition, it engages in the property investment business; wholesale of computer games, sporting, and other recreational goods; and provision of human resource consultancy and cleaning services. The company was formerly known as Niraku Global Community Holdings Inc. Niraku GC Holdings, Inc. was founded in 1950 and is headquartered in Koriyama, Japan.
